OL,3,CCampaigners at Court of Appeal over
OL,4,Ctwo-mile Stonehenge tunnel decision
OL,6,FJames Strachan KC, for the department,
OL,7,Fsaid in written submissions that Mr
OL,8,FMerriman "was not provided with any"
OL,9,Fsummary of representations from SSWHS
OL,10,F"nor even with a summary of National
OL,11,FHighways' position" on the site's
OL,12,Fpreferred route.
OL,14,FMr Merriman "was provided with no
OL,15,Ffurther advice on this issue" of harm
OL,16,Fto Stonehenge, Mr Strachan added.
