OL,3,CCampaigners at Court of Appeal over
OL,4,Ctwo-mile Stonehenge tunnel decision
OL,6,FThe barrister continued: "It was
OL,7,Firrational not to specify the assets
OL,8,Fand consider the level of harm where
OL,9,Fthe minister was purportedly comparing
OL,10,Fthe heritage impacts of two schemes."
OL,12,FPreviously, the National Highways'
OL,13,Fplan was quashed by the High Court in
OL,14,FJuly 2021, due to concerns about the
OL,15,Fenvironmental impact on the site.
OL,17,FHowever, two years later, the tunnel
OL,18,Fwas approved by the Department for
OL,19,FTransport.
